verbose_text: Two samples of H. benthamii (Hbe1 and Hbe2) produced a monoterpene hydrocarbon rich oil characterized by the pre-eminence of alpha-pinene (50.8-51.9%), associated with sesquiterpene hydrocarbons : alpha-copaene (5.4-6.2%), alpha-humulene (3.1-4.4%) and (E)-beta-caryophyllene (1.5-2.3%).
